text: Cape York is the northernmost point of Australia. It was named by Lieutenant James Cook in 1770 after the Duke of York.Frith, D.W., Frith, C.B. (1995). Cape York Peninsula: A Natural History. Chatswood: Reed Books Australia. Reprinted with amendments in 2006. . From the tip, it is about 160 km to New Guinea across the islands, coral reefs and sand banks of Torres Strait. ==References== Category:Geography of Queensland Category:Capes
title: Cape York
